<H3> <TI>   Thai Princess Visits Heilongjiang 13 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401021294 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2200 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1401021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thai Princess Maha Chakkri Sirinthon and her 
entourage, a total of 23 people, arrived in Harbin by train on 
the evening of 13 January. Vice Governor Chen Yunlin received 
her at the railway station. The vice governor extended a warm 
welcome to the Thai princess. The princess thanked him for this. 
  Princess Maha Chakkri Sirinthonn visited China at the 
invitation of the Chinese Government. Before visiting our 
province, she has visited Beijing Municipality, Liaoning 
Province, and Jilin Province. She will pay a five-day visit to 
our province's Harbin and Heihe cities. This is the princess's 
fifth visit to China. 

</TEXT>

