<H3> <TI>   Shandong Building Largest Iron, Steel Production Base </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1501075794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0206 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1501075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jinan, January 15 (XINHUA) -- China is building its 
largest iron and steel production base in Shandong Province. 
  According to an agreement signed here yesterday, the 
Shandong 
Provincial Government is joining hands with Beijing's Capital 
Iron and Steel Complex to build the Qilu Iron and Steel Complex. 
  A local official in charge of the project said 50 billion 
yuan will be required to construct the first phase, scheduled to 
have an annual production capacity of five million tons of steel. 
  After the second construction phase is completed the complex 
will have a designed capacity of 10 million tons of steel a 
year, making it China's largest iron and steel production base. 
  The official noted that the project is being built without 
state investment. It will practise a share-holding system. 

