<F P=103> OW1301163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, January 13 (XINHUA) -- Non-governmental 
scientific research institutes in south China's Guangdong 
Province have flourished in recent years, according to 
government officials. 
  There are now more than 2,000 non-governmental scientific 
and 
technological organizations employing more than 20,000 people. 
  With their technological advantages and flexible operating 
mechanism, these institutes are striving to apply more and more 
scientific and technological results to practical production by 
cooperating with other economic entities. 
  In addition, a number of such institutes are aiming at 
pushing their high-tech products onto international markets by 
setting up Sino-foreign joint ventures. 
  Last year their total output value hit 1.5 billion yuan 
(about 174.2 million U.S. dollars). 

</TEXT>

