<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Minister To Inspect Grain Prices in Hunan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1401152494 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1401152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bai Meiqing, vice minister of the Ministry of 
Internal Trade and concurrently director of the State Grain 
Reserve Administration, came to Changsha City on 9 January to 
inspect how the city controlled grain and oil prices. 
  Accompanied by Vice Governor Zhou Shichang as well as 
provincial and Changsha City grain bureau leaders, Vice Minister 
Bai Meiqing went to grain shops in Wuyi Zhonglu, Renminlu, and 
Taipingjie, where he carefully checked the price tags as well as 
the grain and oil quality and asked about grain and oil sales. 
  To implement instructions of the State Council, 400.5 
million 
kg of grain has been dumped onto the markets throughout the 
province to control grain prices. Grain departments have been 
active in transporting grain and in ensuring variety, quality, 
quantity, prices, and service. Since the period before the New 
Year, all grain departments have openly sold their grain with 
price tags, thus speedily reducing grain and oil prices 
throughout the province. 

</TEXT>

