<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Views Enterprise Internal Management </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301163794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1547 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, January 13 (XINHUA) -- The growth of 
enterprises depends on strict internal management to ensure the 
quality of products, said Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua during a 
two-day inspection tour in Tianjin, a port city in north China. 
  While inspecting a steel-tube company, Zou stressed that in 
addition to appropriate external conditions, enterprises should 
take it as an essential point to expand the market share of 
their products on the basis of fine quality, scheduled delivery 
and good post-sales services. 
  At Tianjin port yesterday, Zou boarded the vessel "Zhenhe," 
China's first fourth-generation container ship, which was 
heading for Europe. 
  He remarked that the vessel's virgin sail indicated that 
China had become one of the countries leading the world in 
container transport, and the port was to become one of the best 
starting points in the "Eurasian bridge." 
  Port officials said that the vessel, equipped with 
state-of-the-art satellite navigation, telecommunications, and 
alarm and unmanned operation systems, is the most up-to-date 
container vessel in the world. 

</TEXT>

