<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Interviews Sudanese Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<H4>   Speaks of `Friendly Relations' </H4>
<F P=102> OW1301060894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0349 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1301060894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondents Wang Yadong (3769 0068 2639) and Li </F>
Houzhi (2621 0624 1807)] 
  [Text] Khartoum, 11 Jan (XINHUA) -- In an interview with 
XINHUA reporters today, Sudanese Foreign Minister Husayn 
Abu-Salih spoke highly of the friendly relations between Sudan 
and China. 
  Salih stated: Despite a series of changes which have taken 
place in the international situation, Sudanese-Chinese relations 
are still enjoying healthy development. This is a result of 
upholding the five principles of peaceful coexistence in their 
foreign policies. 
  Salih added: The forthcoming visit to Sudan by Chinese State 
Council Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen will more 
effectively promote the development of friendly relations 
between the two countries. The Sudanese people are proud of 
their friendship with China. 
  He pointed out: Sudanese-Chinese friendly relations have a 
long history. Sudan was among one of the earliest countries to 
support China's participation in the United Nations. The two 
countries established diplomatic relations as early as 1959. He 
added: The Sudanese people will never forget the Chinese 
people's assistance. In the past, China provided Sudan with 
eight loans which played an important role in Sudan's economic 
development. 
  Salih also stressed that China has consistently supported 
the 
stand of the Third World in international affairs and has won 
the respect of the world's public opinion as well as that of the 
Third World. 

</TEXT>

