  Through the discussion, he added, the two sides have 
achieved 
common understanding in many aspects. The Chinese side is 
optimistic about the prospects of economic and trade cooperation 
between the two countries, he said. 
  Bentsen said that the exchanges between the two sides during 
his visit to China has helped the two countries to make further 
progress in bilateral relations. 
  He said that he expects more meetings with Chinese economic 
leaders, and that the two sides should make efforts so that 
U.S.-Chinese economic relations and trade can continue to 
develop in a healthy manner. 

